          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658224177889-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>crispy hake</strong> to a plate and set aside</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat and once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger paste</strong> and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>remaining cornflour</strong> and <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml]</span> <strong>water </strong>and cook for a further 2 min or until the sauce has thickened and becomes sticky – this is your <strong>spicy hoisin sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658224181166-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
